149. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 2005496179
T1  - Treatment update for anovulation and subfertility in polycystic ovary syndrome
A1  - Mascarenhas M.
A1  - Balen A.H. 
AO  - Mascarenhas, Mariano; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7859-7404
Y1  - 2020//
N2  - This review aims to provide a summary of updates in fertility treatment for women with polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS). The mechanisms through which PCOS causes fertility impairment are summarised in the introductory section with the rest of the review focussing on the different fertility treatment options available in PCOS. The latest evidence on the efficacy and safety profile on first-line (clomiphene citrate and letrozole) and second-line ovulation induction agents (gonadotropins and laparoscopic ovarian drilling) have been discussed with a primary focus on Cochrane reviews on each subject. When both first-line and second-line agents fail to induce ovulation, or in the presence of other fertility pathologies (such as tubal factor or suboptimal sperm parameters), in-vitro fertilisation can be used. Women with PCOS undergoing in-vitro fertilisation have a propensity to develop ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome, and careful consideration needs to be given to individualising the protocol (gonadotropin-releasing hormone antagonist protocol) and ovulation trigger (gonadotropin-releasing hormone agonist trigger) to reduce this risk. The final part of this review focusses on the state of evidence on complementary and adjuvant fertility treatment therapies which have been tried in women with PCOS.Copyright © 2020 Elsevier Ltd
