A1  - Gogokhia N. 
Y1  - 2019//
N2  - Background : Though methylene tetrahydrofolate reductase (MTHFR) gene C677T mutation increases homocysteine level and risk of thrombophilia, connection of these events is not always obvious. Aims : We present a case of C677T homozygous mutation accompanied with thrombophilia. Methods : A 28- year- old woman was investigated according to modern guidelines. Results : A patient resorted hospital with fever 39 O C, fatigue, dyspnea, chest pain, severe pain and edema in left leg, episodes of syncope, dizziness and respiratory insufficiency. 5 years ago in 10- days after appendectomy she developed severe pain, edema in left leg and walking difficulties. Duplex ultrasonography revealed thrombosis of external iliac, common femoral and popliteal veins. MRI confirmed iliofemoral venous thrombosis. On the same day inferior vena cava filter was implanted. After a month she developed pelvic peritonitis. Due to right polycystic ovarium and bilateral pyosalpinx right oophorectomy and left salpingectomy was made. MTHFR gene analysis revealed C677T homozygous mutation and homocysteinemia 20 mumol/L. Patient was treated with Warfarin 5mg/d, Vit B6 , B9 , B12 , Diosmin/hesperidin. Since INR reached 3,0 Warfarin was continued 1,25mg/d. Patient felt well, but last several months she quitted treatment and with above mentioned complains resorted hospital. Coagulation tests were in normal range. CRP was high (65mg/L). CT pulmonary angiography didn ' t reveal embolus in pulmonary arteries. Duplex scan ruled out structural and hemodynamic changes of extra- and intracranial vessels, except basilar arteries with moderate degree spasm, in low extremities thrombosis was not observed. Homocystein level reached 17mumol/L. Fever of unknown etiology, vascular headache, homocysteinemia and chronic vein insufficiency was diagnosed. Patient was treated with antibiotics, Low- molecular Heparin, Warfarin, Vit B6 , B9 , B12 and discharged from clinic. Conclusions : This case shows that MTHFR gene C677T homozygous mutation definitely is linked to homocysteinemia and vein thrombosis but appropriate treatment and monitoring can avoid complications and increase age of healthy life.
