T1  - Introduction to women's imaging - A clinical perspective
A1  - Agarwal S.
A1  - Rastogi R.
A1  - Agarwal A.
A1  - Singh V.P.
A1  - Gupta Y.
A1  - Sharma S. 
Y1  - 2016//
N2  - Soon after its introduction in 1980's, ultrasonography (both transabdominal & transvaginal - TAS & TVS) became an important imaging tool for diagnosing variety of gynecological conditions. Co-ordination of a gynecologist with a radiologist is essential as it ensures optimal imaging results as it tells the radiologist as to what gynecologist desires. It is must to understand that nothing is black nor its pure white but there is always a gray zone. Various imaging modalities if done in coordination can reduce the time & cost in diagnosing a disease. This article is aimed to highlight the major clinical indications of imaging.
