N2  - Objectives: To optimize the surgical correction and reproductive outcomes for females with genital malformations. Design(s): Systematic analysis. Setting(s): Federal Scientific Centre of Obstetrics, Gynaecology and Perinatology, Moscow, Russia Patients: 2,025 patients with various female genital malformations who underwent surgery between 1992 and 2015 Intervention: Endoscopic surgery for women with mullerain anomalies. Clinical investigations included: general clinical examination, karyotyping, ultrasonography, MRI, laparoscopy, hysteroscopy, gonadal morphologic investigation. Measurement and Main Results: 1,854 patients with utero-vaginal anomalies with normal karyotype (46,XX) and 171 females with disorders of sexual development. Surgical reconstruction was performed for: * utero-vaginal aplasia (MRKH syndrome) - Adamyan's laparoscopic peritoneal colpopoesis in 352 cases * uterus duplex in 296 patients, bicornuate uterus in 210 patients * unicornuate uterus - laparoscopic removal of rudimentary horns in 245 cases, * partial vaginal aplasia - vagynoplasty in 240 patients, * septate uterus - hysteroscopic dissection of septum in 445 patients, * cervico-vaginal aplasia in 64 patients - hysterectomy of rudimental uterus in 45 cases; successful creation of the neo-cervical canal with intrauterine stentation in 19 patients. More than 52% of patients had following concomitant infertility factors: tubal and peritoneal adhesions (34%), intrauterine synechia (7%), polycystic ovary (14%) and hormonal disorders, especially anovulation (19%), and ovarian hypofunction (8%). The extra-genital endometriosis was removed in 56% of patients, deep infiltrative endometriosis in 23%, ovarian endometriosis in 6%, and adenomyosis in 8% of cases. Conclusion(s): The endometriosis was still the major cause of pain and infertility in 56% of patients with malformation. The reconstructive surgical correction, assisted reproduction methods and rehabilitation appear to improve reproductive outcomes of 57% women with utero-vaginal anomalies.
