T1  - An efficient infertility evaluation
A1  - Hatasaka H. 
Y1  - 2011//
N2  - The biological clock is a major adversary to human reproduction. Not only does fecundity wane with time, but so does an infertility patient's emotional reserve. Therefore, a well-organized approach to evaluating, treating, and referring patients to subspecialty centers when necessary is critical to optimally manage infertility. The initial infertility evaluation has undergone evidence-based improvements in efficiency and has demonstrated that less testing has given more useful knowledge. © 2011 Lippincott Williams & Wilkins.
