T1  - Pelvic actinomycosis: A rare entity presenting as tubo-ovarian abscess
A1  - Joshi C.
A1  - Sharma R.
A1  - Mohsin Z. 
Y1  - 2010//
N2  - A 24-year-old woman having two children using an intrauterine contraceptive device was admitted with lower abdominal pain and fever. On clinical and radiographic examination revealed a 7 x 6 cm multi-loculated cystic mass in the lower abdomen. The diVerential diagnosis included twisted ovarian cyst, ectopic pregnancy, tubercular tubo-ovarian (TO) mass red degeneration fibroid, diverticular diseases, emphysematous cystitis, pelvic malignancy, and mesenteric cyst. On histologic examination, an actinomycotic TO abscess was found with sulfur granules.
